data.title: Definitely would recommend.
data.text: After reading all reviews we have decided to stop by, and has to say that was excellent. Not only the service was good and the customers service perfect. So friendly and stress free place. We got Brazilian Dish so FRESH. Definitely would recommend

data.title: pizza slices that were good but affordable
data.text: I was in the area visiting my parents, since I do not live nearby, I was looking for a place to eat some pizza slices that were good but affordable and found Cybelles's, the complete experience was very good good, I actually have no complains at all, I remember having ordered slice of pepperoni and a grandma, both were very good, so tasty and crunchy, fresh ingredients and fresh slices, also attention was very good, I will be definitely coming back!

data.title: First time visiting and I felt so welcomed.
data.text: First time visiting and I felt so welcomed.  Staff is wonderful , place is so quaint and inviting.   Great for family and delicious foods. will def be back soon.  I've already gathered a group that's never visited.

data.title: Great Brazilian Style Pizza
data.text: By far the best Brazilian style pizza in the Daly City (SF area). When I have my craving this is the first place I think of. I spent a few years in Brazil when I was younger and I can tell you this is the closest you will get to real authentic Brazil pizza. I usually order for takeout but the restaurant looks like it would have a nice atmosphere if you wanted to sit down and eat.

data.title: Servicable pizza place which also features Brazilian favorites
data.text:
Have gone here about 8 times in the last year...small place which serves pizza, Italian sandwiches and entrees, plus Brazilian cuisine. Place is owned by Brazilian and place is very popular with Brazilians living in the area. Pizza is a step up from Domino's, Round Table, Mountain Mike's, and Costco. Very thick crust and many different toppings.
I have never eaten the Brazilian fare, but I understand it is better than the pizza. Recent staff changes has resulted in a downgrade in customer service.

data.title: Delivery
data.text: Pizza is mostly good, but the soggy middle is aggravating. They need to make it thicker in the middle and cook it hotter.

data.title: Tues Lunch
data.text: Had the parmigiana sandwich it was huge hot and excellent. I had fries and a salad as sides. I ended up taking half the sandwich and the salad for tomorrow's lunch. My coworker had spaghetti that was also very good. It's nice they are close and  do takeout orders.

data.title: Quick and Efficient Deliveryl
data.text: Call for Pizza and Soup.  Both very nice,  but not over the top.  Service time is given,  and they are always right on time.  Service delivery staff has always been very polite,  and clean.

data.title: Lackluster Pizza to go
data.text: The Pizza had no distinct taste.  The sauce had no tang, the crust was soggy and tasteless. the cheese and ingredients seems like it was put together without care. I wonder if the folks here ever taste their pizza?

data.title: Ripoff
data.text:
I ordered the tri-tip diner to be delivered to the Hampton Inn,
which happens to be the most expensive dish on the menu.
I asked the  person who took my order twice that I am not.
 familiar with that cut of meat and I won't order it if its not tender.
He said twice it was. When I received  the food the steak was so tough  I could barely cut it with a knife. I called and said just give me something else. He refused and said next time you order we will take something off the bill. Not acceptable!.

data.title: Brazilian
data.text: Nice place to take family and friends. Brazilian food are one of the best ! I really recomend this place

data.title: California Dreaming
data.text: We ordered takeout to our room after long adventurous day. Pizza was amazing!!! Great food at great price delivered to our hotel what more could you ask for?

data.title: Went here for the Brazilian, was disappointed
data.text: I went here to try the Brazilian food but was sorely disappointed. The salad was not that fresh and the dressing was tasteless and from a bottle. The meat was kind of tough, and the rice and beans were lackluster. The pudim de leite dessert was covered with cheap pancake syrup. Stay away from this place, you can find better pizza and better food in many places.

data.title: Now Serving Excellent Brazilian!
data.text:
Cybelle's has sold to a bunch of Brazilians, who still make pizza, but make awesome Brazilian dinners now too.  On my recent visit I ordered two different things, names were in Portugese, but one was a chicken, and one was steak.
Both were excellent and were loaded with rice, beans, salad.  You get a lot of food for 8 dollars a plate.  Different things are cooked each day.  This is great food!
